description:
After Harvey Dent's face is reconstructed by the brilliant plastic surgeon Dr. Marilyn Crane, he is eventually declared cured and allowed to reenter Gotham society. He starts at a small law firm in Gotham and enters into a relationship with Marilyn.

One day, Marilyn's twin sister Madeliune appears, whom Marilyn had kept a secret because she was afraid she might rekindle Two-Face's obsession with duality. The two sisters never got along, and Marilyn tells Harvey that her sister even tried to murder her on her eleventh birthday.

The more aggressive Madeline seduces Harvey, and they start an affair while Marilyn is blissfully unaware and prepares for her wedding to Harvey. He finally breaks off the affair, but Madeline says that Marilyn does not love the real Harvey the way she herself does, and that she would see her sister in hell before having her take Harvey from her.

Later, Harvey finds Marilyn murdered in her apartment, with "Now it is just the two of us" written in blood on the wall. Harvey wants vengeance, but Harvey Dent is not a killer. He looks at the fire burning in the fireplace, realizing he knows someone who is.

Madeline finds Two-Face on a pier. She is not horrified by his face, she welcomes it. Two-Face kisses her while he shoots her, holding her while she dies in his arms. He then waits for Batman to take him back where he belongs, with the rest of the crazy people.
name: Two of a kind

These are just some of the ingredients of an adventure that concerns once again the myth of King Arthur and tells how the magic sword Excalibur has become the Heilige Lance .

description:
The stars of TORCHWOOD talk exclusively about the new series, MIRACLE DAY, in DOCTOR WHO MAGAZINE 437!

TORCHWOOD, the smash-hit spin-off from Doctor Who, is back for a spectacular new 10-part series. Doctor Who Magazine 437 goes behind the scenes to talk to the cast and crew of this extraordinary adventure, including stars JOHN BARROWMAN (Captain Jack), EVE MYLES (Gwen Cooper), MEKHI PHIFER (Rex Matheson), ALEXA HAVINS (Esther Drummond), KAI OWEN (Rhys Williams), LAUREN AMBROSE (Jilly Kitzinger) and head writer and creator RUSSELL T DAVIES.

DWM asked John Barrowman, could Jack ever return to Doctor Who?

â€œYes, I want to come back!â€ says John. â€œThe beautiful thing aboutDoctor Who is, itâ€™s time travel. Mattâ€™s Doctor could go back before Jack met his Doctor. Or Mattâ€™s Doctor could meet a darker Jack...? Thatâ€™s fine too. There are ways to do it. When heâ€™s in Doctor Who, Jack is very different to the Jack thatâ€™s in Torchwood. Everybody knows my love of Doctor Who, and I would do it at the drop of a hat.â€

ALSO THIS ISSUE:

CALLED TO ACTION! Five remarkable individuals joined the Doctor in his fight against Amyâ€™s kidnappers in A GOOD MAN GOES TO WAR â€“ but could they return to help him again? Find out as DWM talks exclusively to the actors who played them: SIMON FISHER-BECKER (the â€˜fat, old, and blueâ€™ Dorium Maldovar), NEVE McINTOSH (Silurian warrior Madame Vastra), CATRIN STEWART (Victorian maid Jenny), DAN STARKEY (lactating Sontaran Strax) and CHRISTINA CHONG (forest-dwelling soldier Lorna Bucket).

STORYTELLERS Doctor Whoâ€™s showrunner Steven Moffat presents an exclusive guide to the writers of the new series. Find out whoâ€™s a wimp, whoâ€™s a polymath and whoâ€™ll break you heart (twice) in PRODUCTION NOTES...

MASTERPIECES It was the season that gave us Axons, DÃ¦mons and Autons... and which introduced the Doctorâ€™s arch-enemy, the Master! DWM takes a nostalgic look back at the adventures of the Third Doctor, Jo and the Brigadier in 1971â€™s Series Eight, as Countdown to 50! continues.

TIME FOR A SHOCK! As Amy and the Doctor struggle against the ravages of time, theyâ€™re shocked when an old enemy appearsâ€¦ Donâ€™t miss the thrilling final chapter of the latest comic strip adventure, APOTHEOSIS, written by Jonathan Morris with art by Dan McDaid!

ROYâ€™S ROLES
DWM pays tribute to the late ROY SKELTON, the versatile actor who was the voice of dozens of characters, including the Daleks and Cybermen in Doctor Who... and Zippy and George in Rainbow

NICE DAY FOR A WHITE WEDDING Emma, Michael, Chris and Will get their hankies ready as they prepare watch the emotionally-charged, time-twisting Ninth Doctor story FATHERâ€™S DAY. Who will blub and who will retain their composure? Find out in THE TIME TEAM...

HAPPY ANNIVERSARY! To celebrate the release of the 150th audio adventure in the regular monthly range, DWM catches up with the men behind Big Finish. Producers JASON HAIGH-ELLERY, NICHOLAS BRIGGS and DAVID RICHARDSON talk candidly about the past and future of the range â€“ including the new series featuring the Fourth Doctor, Tom Baker...

SPOILT FOR CHOICE? Whatâ€™s best â€“ assiduously avoiding all spoilers, or finding out as much as possible about future episodes of Doctor Who? TOBY HADOKE and JOHNNY CANDON argue the pros and cons in the latest (spoiler-free!) BATTLE OF WITS!

SMUGGLED IN The First Doctor, Ben and Polly enters a world of skullduggery, murder and deceit as they take on a band of merciless pirates â€“ erstwhile crew of the notorious Captain Avery! Join THE FACT OF FICTION as it goes back in time to reveal a treasure trove of secrets concerning the 1966 adventure THE SMUGGLERS...

PLUS! All the latest official news, TV and merchandise reviews, previews, competitions, a prize-winning crossword and much, much more!
name: Barmy Army!

But the reflection gives way to action when Kut Humi calls him and Sergej Orloff to his aid to defend Agarthi from a terrible threat, involving them in an adventure that will allow us , finally , to discover what happened to the murchadna , the ray-gun of Martin.

description: A secret and deadly threat from the past continues to assault the new Green Hornet and Kato. Part two of a four issue storyline that will see everything Britt Reid, Jr. and Mulan have built in the city their fathers once made safe. As their unknown foe tests Green Hornet and Kato with a team of murderous super villains, our heroes have dual missions. They need to figure out who is behind these attacks. They also need to stay alive long enough to do something about it!

description:
FEAR ITSELF TIE-IN It won't take some of the Avengers to fight the madness of Fear Itself it will take ALL OF THEM!! The New Avengers and Avengers join forces in the face of true fear! And who will join the New Avengers for the first time EVER? Stay tuned, True Believer! This is a can't-miss Avengers event!

description:
Hot off the heels of suffering the nightmarish experiments of the man called Contagion, Wolverine is confronted by renegade spacemen Monark Starstalker and Paradox, who have their own set of test theyâ€™d like to run on him. But anyone preparing to stick Logan with needles of techno-organic viruses should be prepared to feel the sharp sting of adamantium claws in the gut. Itâ€™s WOLVERINE: THE BEST THERE IS VS. ROGUE GALACTIC BOUNTY HUNTERS AND THEIR ROBOT FALCON! THUNDERDOME!

The woman who set Wolverine up to be captured by Winsor has transformed into a giant robotic spider virus. Paradox and Monark are there to capture and destroy it. But Paradox is infected by the virus and the spider gets too large for containment. Wolverine is able to hack it down to a containable size and after it has be nuetralized, Monark and Wolverine can turn their attention to Paradox.

Paradox seems to be dieing but changes his body into a Mercurian and burns the virus out of his body. Monark and Paradox take Wolverine back to there ship, to track the rest of the virus and the man who brought it to earth in the first place.

The man , over the years, proved to be inexplicably experienced in the design of computers for military purposes . It's up to Martin to find out how this incident is linked to one of the most mysterious places in the world : Easter Island !

description: With the help of Chris Tower , Martin Mystere is able to foil the plot of the Men in Black , which could lead to a third world war . Then , he moves to Boston, where one of his colleagues at MIT 's shows him a machine he developed : the three-dimensional copier . Someone, however , used the invention to reproduce a mysterious object ...

description: Aboard a submarine of the ancient kingdom of Mu, Martin MystÃ¨re and Java are prisoners of Robinson, an android programmed to conduct a timeless war against humans, who he identified as the descendants of the people of Atlantis. description:
The Japanese goddess Amaterasu is , in fact , the immortal guardian of Yamato , a submarine base of the ancient empire of Mu . Martin Mystere , Java, and Mara Marata must defeat her and the android Robinson , to thwart their plans of war against the entire human race...
Have you ever tried to trace the origin of a joke ? This is the daunting task that it's up to Martin in the new adventure that awaits him in the second half of the issue.

New York has been INFESTED and the web grows as it gets ready to explode into SPIDER-ISLAND! Normal people are getting Spider-Powers! But not all of them realize that with great power must also come â€¦.you know the rest. Okay, sure we often say Peter Parkerâ€™s life will never be the same. But listen, pal, weâ€™ve never been more serious. Heroes and villains are crawling all over Manahttan and no one knows why. This will change everything for Pete, for Spideyâ€¦and possibly for YOU! Chuslamacree is a small village in the Irish countryside . Martin and Java are here to investigate a small but unexplained plane crash . It soon became clear that the mysteries of Chuslamacree are quite different , and a strange series of events culminating with the disappearance of a little girl named Lilian . She was probably kidnapped by the Fairy People , a community of elves , goblins , leprechauns , gremlins and goblins.

The literary case of the unfinished novel by Charles Dickens , " The Mystery of Edwin Drood " is , however , one of the ingredients of the story that kicks off at the close of this book .

For the past year, Bruce Banner has fought gods and monsters to protect his family and everything he holds dear, but now heâ€™s up against the toughest foe the angriest man on the planet has ever faced â€“ his own shocking desires. When a genuine wishing well is unleashed upon the Marvel Universe, everyoneâ€™s true yearnings are fulfilled. But between what we think we want and what we truly desire may lie a terrifying chasm â€“ made all the more dangerous by Umar of the Dark Dimension and Armageddon, Warlord of the Troyjan!

All of which leaves Volstagg and Kid Loki in charge of the Shining City for an afternoon. What could possibly go wrong?

Alle finds herself mysteriously in a world unknown and dangerous. Hank, who notes that everyone has gone, try to find out what is happening by talking to his cat Sparkles. Sudana, a woman who seems very powerful, may have some answers to his questions.

At Trowbridge - United Kingdom, Samsun made an appearance.

The cast of 'Douche Beach,' the Pouperheus Sisters, Lady Art Projekt, even teen heart throb Kendall Schipp and his millions of 'Worschippers'... none are safe from the Fame Monster! Back ups include Hoax Hunters by Steve Seeley, Michael Moreci, and JM Ringuet, and The Corpse by James Lowder and Jean-Paul Deshong.

description: THE HOTTEST NEW BOOK IN COMICS IS BACK WITH A SPIDER-ISLAND PRELUDE! Can the new Venom and Peter Parker (The Amazing Spider-Man) put aside their differences to help save a man from himself? Plus Betty Brant, crusading blogger and gal pal to Flash Thompson may be onto the secrets behind the infestation kicking off this summerâ€™s Spider-Blockbuster! Rick Remender (X-FORCE) joins Tony Moore (FRANKEN-CASTLE) and Tom Fowler (I AM AN AVENGER) for the next crucial chapter in the life of Flash Thompson!Â

description: Green Hornet and Kato have inspired a new duo of costumed crimefighters in Los Angeles. Too bad they believe Green Hornet is a criminal and want him dead. Also, the Triad strike back with explosive results.

description: The Triad think they have the Green Hornet and his sidekick, but they have a pair of Sentinel employees instead. Can Green Hornet and Kato save their friends in time? And what happens when other costumed vigilantes, cops, and federal agents make the scene? The conclusion to the movie sequel may spell the end of the Green Hornet and Kato!

description: The first issue of the all-new, Kevin Smith vision of Kato to take place after the events of Smith's first smash Green Hornet arc. The complex relationship between the new Kato and the new Green Hornet grows as Kato battles new foes and finds new a new friend.

description: What classic noir revenge tale would be complete without a femme fatale? When a mysterious woman saves Alec King and offers to get him out of his current predicament, will Alec's past collide violently with his present? Or will his need to avenge Brian's death overcome his normal need for self-preservation?

description:
In the early 60s, the space race was moving towards its climax. Prior to manned spaceflight, both Americans and Soviets were launching animals up in rockets in order to test the biological viability of manned spaceflight... often with tragic results.

Extensively researched, First in Space is based on the true story of Ham, a chimpanzee that NASA trained for the first sub-orbital spaceflight. This rousing adventure provides a snapshot in time of mankindÃ¯Â¿Â½s early steps at conquering the final frontier.

The insidious cult of the Loveking is spreading through Carson Napier's kingdom on the ocean world of Venus. If Carson can't break the Loveking's spell, the balance of power on Venus will be shattered and the woman Carson loves will be lost to him forever. But a jungle howl from a faraway world signals the arrival of a powerful ally, Tarzan, whom Carson will desperately need to avert disaster on his adopted planet! Also included in this volume is "Tarzan: A Tale of Mugambi," never before collected!

volume.name: Edgar Rice Burroughs' Tarzan/Carson of Venus

description: Casey Williams and her fellow grad students have a rather interesting homework assignment: decrypt a recently discovered Nazi code left over from World War 2. But as they begin their work, those connected with it are found dead. Casey knows hat there's more to the "Enigma Cipher" than map coordinates from a sixty-year-old war, but in order to save her own life she'll have to crack the code!

description: Nick Corrigan is unemployed, behind on the rent, and his girlfriend cheats on him. Things start To look up when he discovers that his neighbor used to be "Hardliner," the notorious supervillain. With nothing left to lose, Nick blackmails his neighbor into training him to become a career super-criminal because being bad feels good when you try it.

With the threat of exposure looming over his head, Charlie Cobb is blackmailed into teaching Nick Corrigan how to use his old Hardliner armor... though he'd rather rip the kid's throat out than help him. Nick is a fast study, despite several suspicious training "accidents." Meanwhile, a mysterious FBI agent investigates the murder of Nick's former boss, and informs Nick's girlfriend Sam that her boyfriend could be the killer.

The two men settle into a shaky truce as Charlie continues to teach Nick how to be a super-criminal. Nick plans out his first big heist, but he suspects Cobb is plotting something. His worst fears are confirmed when his attempted robbery is interrupted by the city's patron hero, The Flying Ace.

The conflict brewing between Nick and Charlie Cobb finally reaches the boiling point. Cobb will do anything to get out from under Nick's thumb, but when Cobb betrays his student and hands him over to The Flying Ace, it turns out the famous hero has some plans of his own!
